{
  "texts": [
    "Each graph is annotated with a binary label 𝑦 𝑖 ∈ {0, 1}, indicating whether the graph is an outlier (𝑦 𝑖 = 1) or not (𝑦 𝑖 = 0).",
    "The objective of the task is to learn a function 𝑓: G → {0, 1} that predicts the binary label ŷ𝑖 for each graph G 𝑖. Dataset ConstructionTo support outlier detection on TAG, we construct three fake news detection (sub-)datasets in the same format as Datasetfoot_0 in PyG, based on existing datasets.",
    "For Politifact and Gossipcop, we follow [14] and [4], which jointly models news content and user interaction through propagation graphs.",
    "While the original datasets provided only preprocessed text embeddings via BERT or word2vec as node features, we retain the raw textual content of both the news articles and user historical posts, allowing for more flexibility in LLM-based methods.",
    "For Fakeddit, we adopt all samples in [13] as news content, and represent comment usersfoot_1 as child nodes in the graph."
  ]
}